To answer your two questions:

CONFIG_IA64_GENERIC is NOT selected when CONFIG_IA64_SGI_SN2 is selected. It doesn't exist in our Kconfig at all, and we don't define it anywhere. This is intentional — it was the machvec "build all platforms" option. Two places in SN2 code reference it (sn2/io.c and sn/kernel/Makefile), but both compile to nothing under !CONFIG_IA64_GENERIC, which is correct for our approach since those were machvec function pointer wrappers.

CONFIG_IA64_GENERIC was NOT renamed to CONFIG_IA64. They were always separate. CONFIG_IA64 is the arch flag (always y). When SN2 was removed, the "System type" choice menu containing IA64_GENERIC, IA64_DIG, IA64_SGI_SN2, etc. was deleted entirely, and DIG-like defaults (select ACPI, select SWIOTLB, select PCI_MSI, etc.) were baked unconditionally into config IA64.

The updated patch 0003 now makes three things conditional on !IA64_SGI_SN2 in config IA64:

    select SWIOTLB if !IA64_SGI_SN2 — SN2 has its own DMA via SHUB
    select ARCH_HAS_DMA_COHERENT_TO_PFN if SWIOTLB — only needed with SWIOTLB
    select ARCH_HAS_SYNC_DMA_FOR_CPU if SWIOTLB — same

